====Trivia====
A holdover from [[Middle English]], ''yclept'' is one of a small number of English words where ''y'' figures as a {{glossary|vowel}} at the beginning of a word. Others include {{m|en|Yngling}}, {{m|en|ytterbium}}, and {{m|en|yttrium}}.
